stimulus: Welcome to the experiment. Press any key to begin.

You will see a list of words and colored squares in the following task.

Press the spacebar whenever you see a GREEN square.

Do not press a key if the square is RED.

Press the spacebar to continue.

Please try to remember as many of the words as you can, and try to think about the meaning of each word as it appears.

After the detection and encoding task you will be asked to solve some math problems for 24 seconds.

Please solve as many problems as you can in the time given.

Press the spacebar to continue.

After solving the math problems, you will be asked to type in as many words

from the previous list as you can remember for 75 seconds.

If you finish recalling before the 75 seconds are up,

just sit tight and try to think of any more words you could have missed.

Press the spacebar to continue.

There will be 16 lists of words and recall, followed by

a recognition phase. The experiment is expected to take up to 90 minutes.

We will begin with a brief practice session.

Press the spacebar to begin the practice.

You will now begin the recognition phase of the experiment.

A word will appear on the screen, and you will be asked whether you think the word was shown

previously during the experiment. Press B if you think the item is OLD (i.e., has been shown before)

and press N if you think the item is NEW (i.e., was not shown previously during the experiment).

Press the spacebar to continue.

After indicating whether you think the item is old or new,

you will be asked to indicate how sure you feel that your choice is correct.

Use the number keys to indicate from 1 to 7 how confident you are that your response of old or new was accurate.

Please try to use to full range of number choices to indicate your confidence.

Press the spacebar to continue.

After providing your confidence ratings,

you will be asked which color square the word may have appeared with,

as well as whether the square appeared above or below the word.

Please try your best to remember the color and position of the square that appeared with each word.

Use the arrow keys to indicate your response.

Press the spacebar to begin the recognition section.
